definitions.definition: The second in a series , especially, the second of an artist’s albums or the second of four years in a high school ( tenth grade ) or university.
examples: The band’s sophomore album built upon the success of their debut release, catapulting them to megastardom.

main_definition: ( US ) The second in a series , especially, the second of an artist’s albums or the second of four years in a high school ( tenth grade ) or university.
